<SBODY>3 3 6
WARRANTY <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">DEED</ENAMEX>.
This <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">Indenture</ENAMEX>, Made this <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">day of
in the year
of our Lord one thousand eight hundred and seventy four</TIMEX> Between <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Elizabeth Secrited</ENAMEX> formerly
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Elizabeth Rudolph</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Buffalo</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">New York</ENAMEX>
of the first part, and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Thomas McKay</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Oleca Cattaraugus</ENAMEX> County
of the second part
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Wis</ENAMEX>, That the said party of the first part, in consideration of the sum of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">four hundred
Dollars</NUMEX>,
to be duly paid, hath sold, and by these presents do grant and convey to the said party of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX>,
and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>, ALL THAT TRACT OR PARCE OF LAND, situate in the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Village of Olera</ENAMEX> in the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of
Cataraugus</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX> and Known as the east undivided <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">one
half</NUMEX> part of all that piece or parcel of land described on a map of
<ENAMEX TYPE="COREF.loc">said Village</ENAMEX> made by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">J.J. Gossline</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="TITLE">Esq.</ENAMEX> and which said map is now
on file in the office of the <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Comptroller</ENAMEX> of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX> as Block
seventy six ( <ENAMEX TYPE="AGE">76</ENAMEX>) in said <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">village of Oliver</ENAMEX>, containing <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">two ( 2)</NUMEX> acres be the
same more or less,
The party of the first part to put the party of second part in possession
of said premises at <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> own costs & expeace.
Wit SppurtaHEES, and all the estate, title and interest therein of the said party of the first part. And the said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Elizabeth
Secretter</ENAMEX> formerly <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Elizabeth Rudolph</ENAMEX>
doth hereby covenant and agree to and with the said party of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>
that the premises thus conveyed, in the quiet and peaceable possession of the said party of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>,
will forever WARRANT AND DEFEND against any person <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">whomsoever</ENAMEX> lawfully claiming the same or any part thereof.
In Witness whereof, The party of the first part, hath hereunto set <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> hand and seal the <TIMEX TYPE="COREF.dat">day and year first above written</TIMEX>.
Sealed and Delivered in Presence of
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Elizabeth Sureiter</ENAMEX> ℗
[ L.S.]
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">STATE OF NEW YORK</ENAMEX>, S.
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">CATTARAGUS COUNTY</ENAMEX>.
<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">ninth day of
seventy four</TIMEX> before <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX>, the subscriber, personally appeared <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Elizabeth Secrister</ENAMEX> to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX> known to be the same persons described in and <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">who</ENAMEX> executed the within
instrument, and severally acknowledged that <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">they</ENAMEX> executed the same, and the said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Elizabeth</ENAMEX>
on a private examination by <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX>, apart from <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> said <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">husband</ENAMEX>, acknowledged that <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">she</ENAMEX> executed the same freely, and without any fear or compulsion of <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> said <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">husband</ENAMEX>.
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">L. J. Lawton</ENAMEX>,
Record and an end in the
</SBODY>
</NBX>
